commit.message:
Make the character used for indentation in pretty mode a parameter

Now the "indent" argument to dump() may be also a string, allowing a different character
than the default space for the indentation of the prettified JSON.

This fixes issue #135.
Cosmetic, use a consistent style in if statements adding braces everywhere
Use PEP 489 multiphase initialization
Update CHANGES.rst

Avoid warning about unknown pytest marker

Remove pytest.mark.unit decoration on test function, it is not necessary and modern pytest
emits a warning about undefined marker.
Handle Python 3.6 difference in timedelta representation
Cosmetic, split overly long lines, fix indentation and whitespace issues
catch more non-time values
fix 7, 8 and 9 digit fractions, add more tests
fix negative offset issue, add test for negative offset
Add support for 1-9 fractional seconds
Recompute benchmarks tables using Python 3.8.2 and latest rapidjson
Upgrade underlying rapidjson library to its current master

Add orjson and hyperjson to the benchmarks and renew comparison tables

This addresses issue #130. Thanks to Sebastian Pipping for initial implementation (see
PR #131) and research.
Fix typos in Makefile help targets
Use cibuildwheel 1.1.0
Avoid Sphinx warning using currentmodule directive
Switch to Ubuntu bionic, to use the debug build of Python 3.6

Use default MacOS image and select Python 3.8 in the osx build

This should fix the CI build on MacOS, that started to fail with a "strange" message
coming from brew:

  https://travis-ci.org/python-rapidjson/python-rapidjson/jobs/653073726#L4239

Selecting a specific Python version seems enough, so the "brew upgrade python" is not
needed anymore.

Merge pull request #129 from timgates42/bugfix/typo_tolerance

Fix simple typo: tollerance -> tolerance

commit.message:
Add Python 3.8 classifier and remove Python 3.4

The latter reached its EOL in March 2019, and cibuildwheel 1.0.0 dropped support for
it (see https://github.com/joerick/cibuildwheel/pull/168).
Release 0.9.1
Update CHANGES.rst

Free the error object associated to the ValidationError exception

This fixes issue #126.
Release 0.9.0
Update CHANGES.rst

Revert "Use python 3.6 on travis, as that seems the current default version"

Apparently the only debug build of Python is still version 3.5.

This reverts commit ec46ea4e0f92ba410ec506b262b8e6f86bf9d871.
Use python 3.6 on travis, as that seems the current default version
Use cibuildwheel 1.0.0, to produce Python 3.8 wheels
